Once there was a king named Midas
He was a very greedy king, he liked gold a lot, once he was visited by god himself and because 
he treated god really well, god was pleased and asked hima any wish.
On being asked, he told that he wanted to turn anything into gold that he touched,
God granted him the wish, after that he was happy and touched his walls, it turned into gold.
He touched his bed, it turned into gold. He was very happy, he was called for lunch by his servent 
he touched the food, it turned into gold, and then his daughter came to him and he hugged her, and she turned into
gold. He cried because he couldn't undo the damaage. He asked god to remove his powers and bring back his daughter,

Morale of the story: Something good always comes with consequences